HEADWORD: Geophilomorpha
<hw>Geophilomorpha</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>an order of myriopod
arthropods containing elongated centipedes living in soil and under
stones and having more than 30 pairs of legs.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> order <ord>Geophilomorpha</ord>.</syn>⟦br⟧
